== Use ==
You can use {{tlg|long comment|subst=yes}} to prevent a page thus redirected from being listed on [[Special:Shortpages]].

; <nowiki>{{Wiktionary redirect}} {{subst:long comment}}</nowiki> : Provides a [[Wikipedia:Soft redirect|soft redirect]] to the Wiktionary page, using the current page's name, but the ''first letter is turned to lower case''. '''Check''' if the case is appropriate.

{{wiktionary redirect}}
{{clear}}

; <nowiki>{{wtr|sophisticated}} {{subst:long comment}}</nowiki> : Pass a parameter to specify the link target.

{{wiktionary redirect|sophisticated}}
{{clear}}

; <nowiki>{{wtr|Category:English idioms|many=yes}}</nowiki> : Pass {{para|many|yes}} to link to lists or categories on Wiktionary.
{{wiktionary redirect|Category:English idioms|many=yes}}
{{clear}}

; <nowiki>{{wtr|mokkori|italic=yes}}</nowiki> : Pass {{para|italic|yes}} to comply with [[:en:MOS:FOREIGNITALIC|MOS:FOREIGNITALIC]] for foreign-language words.
{{Wiktionary redirect|mokkori|italic=yes}}
{{clear}}

==Side effects==
# This template will categorise tagged articles into [[:Category:Redirects to Wiktionary]].

